The hover effect is achieved by specifying a different color for the `:hover` pseudo-class of the anchor tags. When the cursor hovers over any of the anchor tags, the text color will change to the specified color (in this case, blue) due to the hover effect we defined in CSS.

Remember, you can customize the styling and hover effect to match your own preferences and design requirements.

